<subSubSection id="C3EC652E1615FFABFF2BF99BFCE3FDF6" pageId="1" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B4936A51615FFABFF2BF99BFCE3FDF6" blockId="1.[151,1436,1598,1934]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71615FFABFF2BF99BFEC2FC20" bold="true" box="[151,273,1598,1624]" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Leafhoppers with anterior margin of crown varying from rounded to narrowly rounded (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201615FFABFAF4F99BFA44FC20" box="[1352,1431,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201615FFABFF2BF9C0FF64FC07" box="[151,183,1637,1663]" captionStart="FIGURES 58–65" captionStartId="16.[151,269,1886,1910]" captionTargetBox="[164,1421,217,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-71@16.[151,1436,194,1862]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURES 58–65. Exogonia una sp. nov., male holotype: (58) body, lateral view; (59) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (60) pygofer, lateral view; (61) valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; (62) connective and style, dorsal view; (63) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (64) paraphyses, lateral view; (65) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321380" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321380/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">59</figureCitation>
), crown with epicranial, temporal, and frontogenal sutures usually visible. Pronotum generally with width approximately equal to transocular width; lateral margins convergent anteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201615FFABFBF1F929FB45FCDE" box="[1101,1174,1676,1702]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–8" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1672,1696]" captionTargetBox="[163,1416,195,1621]" captionTargetId="figure-91@3.[151,1436,169,1647]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–8. Exogonia capixaba sp. nov., male holotype: (1) body, lateral view; (2) head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; (3) pygofer, lateral view (illustrated mounted on a temporary slide with glycerin); (4) subgenital plate, ventral view; (5) connective and style, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (7) paraphyses, lateral view; (8) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321356/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); dorsopleural carinae complete and oblique; posterior pronotal margin concave medially. Male pygofer strongly produced posteriorly, apical margin convex, usually with pair of ventral processes on apical portion bearing numerous setae (
